      ],
      "markdown": "## The Quotient Rule \n\nWe find a rule for differentiating the quotient of two differentiable functions $u=f(x)$ and $v=g(x)$ in much the same way that we found the Product Rule.\n\nIf $X,U,$ and vchange by amounts $\\Delta\\boldsymbol{X},\\Delta\\boldsymbol{U},$ and $\\Delta V.$ ,then the corresponding change in the quotient u/vis \n\n$$\\begin{array}{c}{\\displaystyle\\Delta\\Bigg(\\frac{u}{v}\\Bigg)=\\frac{u+\\Delta u}{v+\\Delta v}-\\frac{u}{v}=\\frac{(u+\\Delta u)v-u(v+\\Delta v)}{v(v+\\Delta v)}}\\\\ {\\displaystyle}\\\\ {\\displaystyle=\\frac{v\\Delta u-u\\Delta v}{v(v+\\Delta v)}}\\end{array}$$",
